  "description": [
    "TO WELL liiLI TOOM VOLUME 4 ROSWELL NEW MEXICO MONDAY EVENING JANUARY 14 1907 NUMBER 269 Clarence Ullery The Undertake t0 has 7 his Space JORDON ON JAPS COLLEGE MAN SPEAKS ON THE ASIATIC PROBLEM A HOODLUM AGT He So Characterizes a Japanese Ex clusion Act Safest for a Citizen to Be a Gentleman Jordan Be lieves Japan Is Sincere San Francisco Cal Jan 14 No gress could pass a Japanese exclus ion act said David Starr Jordan president of Lelan1 Stanford Univer sity in addressing a meeting at Equity Hall last night of Socialists by whom he had been invited to speak on the Asiatic problem and no President would sign one be cause it would be a hoodlum act Jordan quoted President Roosevelt in saying that as a general rule it is safest for a citizen to be a gentle man and said that he was of the opinion that the remedy of the immi gration troubles did not lie in law lessness nor yet in mass meetings denouncing the Japanese as a nation because they did not go to the same Sunday school we attend It is all nonsense he said that we have to fight with"
